# X · a codex of PHONETIKOS

a codex-emergent of the PHN universe — the codex · the symbol of the unknown and the unnamed. moniker ⟦X:PHN:61036f⟧

**who —** from the illiterate hand that drew an X in place of a name to the X Malcolm took for the name slavery erased — the same absence, drawn the same way.
**what —** X — the letter we reach for when we cannot name a thing: the unknown quantity, the unknown ray, the unmarked grave, the stolen name.
**where —** Greek chi/xi to Roman ten to Descartes' algebra to the illiterate's mark to Malcolm X
**why —** because a culture needs a single placeholder for 'here is something whose name we don't have,' and X — already the unknown of algebra and the mark of the nameless — became that placeholder everywhere
**how —** one crossed shape pressed into service wherever a true name is missing — the variable, the ray, the spy, the buried spot, the unwritten signature, the stolen surname

**the seal —** X is the letter of the unknown and the unnamed; reach for it whenever the true name is missing.

> a catalogued codex under the DLW standard — honestly sourced; the paper marks what is
